      <h1 class="blog-title">Letters to You: Writing to Your Child Inside the Book</h1>

      <p class="blog-meta">Feature &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp; 3 min read</p>

      <div class="blog-body">

        <p>The Letters to You section is where family members write letters directly to your child — words that appear in the book website as actual letter-style cards.</p>

        <p>This section is part of the paid plan.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>What's in a letter</h2>

        <p>Each letter has five fields:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>From</strong> — who the letter is from (Mom, Dad, Grandma, anyone)</li>
          <li><strong>Occasion</strong> — when or why it was written (at birth, first birthday, just because)</li>
          <li><strong>Salutation</strong> — the opening line ("Dear little one," or "To my son,")</li>
          <li><strong>Body</strong> — the full letter</li>
          <li><strong>Signature</strong> — the sign-off ("With all my love, Mom")</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Add as many letters as you want. There's no limit.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>How it looks on the website</h2>

        <p>On the website, each letter displays as a letter-style card — salutation, body, and signature laid out the way a real written letter reads. Letters scroll one after another.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Who writes them</h2>

        <p>Usually parents write the first letters. But the section is open-ended — grandparents can text you the words and you type them in, siblings can dictate one, a close friend who was there. The letters don't have to be from the parents alone.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>Editing from the app or the web</h2>

        <p>The Letters editor is available in the iOS/Android app and in the web editor at legacyodyssey.com/account/book/letters. Writing a longer letter is usually easier from a keyboard.</p>

        <div class="blog-cta-box">
          <p><strong>Your child's own .com, their own book.</strong></p>
          <a href="/#pricing" class="btn-primary">Get Started &rarr;</a>
        </div>

        <p class="blog-footer-note"><em>Legacy Odyssey is a digital baby book platform. Every family gets their own private .com, unlimited photo storage, and a Time Vault to seal letters until the day you choose. <a href="https://legacyodyssey.com">Start your baby's site today &rarr;</a></em></p>

